The paper discusses a new algorithm for one-bit compressed sensing, which involves the recovery of sparse signals from sign measurements. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also mentions the use of consistent reconstruction, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is designed to solve a convex and unconstrained subproblem, which suggests the use of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents numerical experiments to compare the performance of the algorithm, which is a common practice in statistical learning (cs.SI).
